Colias wiskotti is a butterfly in the family Pieridae. It is found in Turkestan, Uzbekistan, Afghanistan, Tajikistan, and Kashmir. The habitat consists of xerophytic mountains.It is a highly polymorphous species with a lot of varieties or forms described. Adults are on wing from June to August.The larvae feed on Acantolimon, Oxytropis, and Onobrychis echidna.